  "text": "2) The microstructures are quite abundant. Their number in a normal petrographic thin section (2.8 × 4.7 cm in width and 30 µm in thickness) can be 100 or more. Colony-like clusters of lenses and spheres are common, and paired specimens as well [CITATION_1] .",
